---
import Site from '../../layouts/Site.astro'
import Section from '../../components/container/Section.astro'
import Link from '../../components/elements/Link.astro'
import { Var } from '../../script/var'
---

<Site
  title={`${Var.app.name} — ${Var.app.tagline}`}
  description={Var.app.description}
>
  <Section>
    <article>
      <h1>Terms of Service</h1>
      <p>
        <strong>Updated on September 18, 2024</strong>. This policy is adapted
        from the <Link
          href="https://github.com/basecamp/policies"
          target="_blank">Basecamp Open-Source Policies</Link
        > / <Link
          href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/"
          target="_blank">CC BY 4.0</Link
        >
      </p>
      <br />
      <p>
        When you use {Var.app.name} you are agreeing to these latest Terms of Service
        (“Terms”). Violation of these terms may, result in termination your account.
      </p>
      <p>
        We may update these Terms of Service at any time. If we make significant
        changes, we will refresh the date at the top of this page.
      </p>
      <p>Kindly read these Terms before signing up or using {Var.app.name}.</p>
      <div class="separator"></div>
      <h2>Contents</h2>
      <ul class="bullet-list left-margin">
        <li>
          <Link href="#definitions">Definitions</Link>
        </li>
        <li>
          <Link href="#account-terms">Account Terms</Link>
        </li>
        <li>
          <Link href="#payments-refunds-plan-changes">Payments & Refunds </Link>
        </li>
        <li>
          <Link href="#cancellation-and-termination">Account Deletion</Link>
        </li>
        <li>
          <Link href="#modification-to-the-service-prices"
            >Modification to {Var.app.name}</Link
          >
        </li>
        <li>
          <Link href="#uptime-security-privacy">Uptime, Security & Privacy</Link
          >
        </li>
        <li>
          <Link href="#copyright-and-content-ownership"
            >Copyright & Content Ownership
          </Link>
        </li>
        <li>
          <Link href="#services-adaptations">Services Adaptations</Link>
        </li>
        <li>
          <Link href="#liability">Liability</Link>
        </li>
      </ul>
      <div id="definitions" class="separator"></div>
      <h2>Definitions</h2>
      <p>
        “We”, “our”, or “us” in this policy, refers to {Var.app.name}.
      </p>

      <p>
        “You” or “your” refers to the people or organizations that own an
        account with us. An account is owned by an organization if it is a legal
        entity.
      </p>
      <p>
        If the organization is unincorporated, the account is owned by the
        individual who signed up for the account.
      </p>
      <div id="account-terms" class="separator"></div>
      <h2>Account Terms</h2>
      <ol class="left-margin">
        <li>
          <p>
            You are responsible for maintaining the security of your account and
            password. We will not be liable for any loss or damage from your
            failure to comply with this security obligation.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p id="user-restriction-list">
            <span><strong>User Restriction Policy</strong></span>
            &mdash; You may not use {Var.app.name} for any purpose outlined below:
          </p>
          <ul class="bullet-list left-margin">
            <li>Use {Var.app.name} to break any laws or regulations.</li>
            <li>Gather or use information from accounts that aren’t yours.</li>
            <li>
              Attempt to deceive us or other users by making false reports or
              pretending to be someone else.
            </li>
            <li>
              Bypass or interfere with the security features of {Var.app.name}.
            </li>
            <li>
              Overload or disrupt any configuration or operations of
              {Var.app.name}.
            </li>
            <li>
              Send or try to send viruses or any malware, or add tracking tools
              like web bugs and cookies to {Var.app.name}.
            </li>
            <li>Harass or threaten other users, or anyone from our team.</li>
            <li>
              <p>
                In addition to the above, We reserve the right to suspend or
                cancel any account, at any time, without notice.
              </p>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            You are responsible for all content posted to and activity that
            occurs under your account.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            You must be a human. Accounts registered by “bots” or other
            automated methods are not permitted.
          </p>
        </li>
      </ol>
      <div id="payments-refunds-plan-changes" class="separator"></div>
      <h2>Payments & Refunds</h2>
      <p>
        <span><strong>{Var.app.name} is free to use</strong></span>. However,
        you can <Link href="./support-us"
          >Support us via financial contribution
        </Link>. Such acts of charity is considered conscious and voluntary,
        hence non-refundable.
      </p>
      <div id="cancellation-and-termination" class="separator"></div>
      <h2>Account Deletion</h2>
      <ol class="left-margin">
        <li>
          <p>
            You are solely responsible for properly deleting your account. You
            will find the option to delete your account under Accounts section.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            An email request to delete your account is not automatically
            considered deletion. If you need help to delete your account, kindly
            mail us at: <Link
              href=`mailto:${Var.app.contact.email}`
              target="_blank">{Var.app.contact.email}</Link
            >
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            All of your content will be deleted from {Var.app.name} immediately upon
            account deletion. We cannot recover your data once it has been deleted.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            We reserve the right to suspend or terminate your account and refuse
            any and all current use of {Var.app.name} for any reason at any time.
          </p>
          <p>
            Suspension means you will not be able to access the account or any
            content in the account.
          </p>
          <p>
            Termination will furthermore result in the deletion of your account
            or your access to your account, and the deletion of all content in
            your account.
          </p>
          <p>
            We also reserve the right to refuse the use of {Var.app.name} to anyone
            for any reason at any time, including, but not limited to violations
            of our <Link href="#user-restriction-list"
              >User Restrictions Policy</Link
            >.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            Verbal, physical, written or other abuse (including threats of abuse
            or retribution) of our team or other users will result in immediate
            account termination.
          </p>
        </li>
      </ol>
      <div id="modification-to-the-service-prices" class="separator"></div>
      <h2>Modification to {Var.app.name}</h2>
      <ol class="left-margin">
        <li>
          <p>
            We intend to support {Var.app.name} as far as it is possible and reasonable
            to do so.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            We reserve the right at any time to modify or discontinue,
            temporarily or permanently, {Var.app.name} with or without notice.
          </p>
        </li>
      </ol>
      <div id="uptime-security-privacy" class="separator"></div>
      <h2>Uptime, Security & Privacy</h2>
      <ol class="left-margin">
        <li>
          <p>
            Your use of {Var.app.name} is at your sole risk. We provide this service
            on an “as is” and “as available” basis. We do not offer service-level
            agreements, but do take uptime of our platform seriously.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            We reserve the right to temporarily disable your account if your
            usage significantly exceeds the average usage of other users of {
              Var.app.name
            }.
          </p>
          <p>
            We’ll reach out to the account owner before taking any action except
            in rare cases where the level of use may negatively impact the
            performance of the {Var.app.name} for other customers.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            We take many measures to protect and secure your data through
            backups, redundancies, and encryption. We enforce encryption for
            data transmission from the public Internet.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            You agree that {Var.app.name} may process your data as described in our
            <Link href="./privacy-policy" target="_blank">Privacy Policy</Link> and
            for no other purpose.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            We use third party vendors and hosting partners to provide the
            necessary hardware, software, networking, storage, and related
            technology required to run {Var.app.name}.
          </p>
        </li>
      </ol>
      <div id="copyright-and-content-ownership" class="separator"></div>
      <h2>Copyright & Content Ownership</h2>
      <ol class="left-margin">
        <li>
          <p>
            All content posted on {Var.app.name} must comply with Indian copyright
            law.
          </p>
        </li>

        <li>
          <p>
            You may not duplicate, copy, or reuse any portion of the HTML, CSS,
            JavaScript, or visual design elements without express written
            permission from {Var.app.name}.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            You must request permission to use our logo for promotional
            purposes. Please email us at <Link
              href={`mailto:${Var.app.contact.email}`}
              target="_blank">{Var.app.contact.email}</Link
            > for permission.
          </p>
          <p>
            We reserve the right to rescind any permissions if you violate these
            Terms.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            You agree not to reproduce, duplicate, copy, sell, resell or exploit
            any portion of {Var.app.name}, use of {Var.app.name}, or access to {
              Var.app.name
            } without our written permission.
          </p>
        </li>
      </ol>
      <div id="services-adaptations" class="separator"></div>
      <h2>Services Adaptations</h2>
      <ol class="left-margin">
        <li>
          <p>
            You expressly understand and agree that we are not liable for any
            damages or losses resulting from your use of {Var.app.name}.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            Abuse or excessively frequent requests to {Var.app.name} via the API
            may result in the temporary or permanent suspension of your account’s
            access.
          </p>
          <p>
            {Var.app.name}, in its sole discretion, will determine abuse or
            excessive usage of the API.
          </p>
          <p>
            If we need to suspend your account’s access, we will attempt to warn
            the account owner first.
          </p>
          <p>
            If your API usage could or has caused downtime, we may cut off
            access without prior notice.
          </p>
        </li>
      </ol>
      <div id="liability" class="separator"></div>
      <h2>Liability</h2>
      <p>
        You agree that {Var.app.name} is not liable to you or to any third party
        for damages of any kind that result from the use of {Var.app.name}, in
        ability to access data, or unauthorized access of your data or account.
      </p>
      <p>
        {Var.app.name} is also not liable for damages of any kind related to actions
        of any third party that uses our platform, or any other consequences related
        to the Terms or Services.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong
          >If you have a question about any of these Terms, please <Link
            href="/support"
            target="_blank">contact us</Link
          >.</strong
        >
      </p>
    </article>
  </Section>
</Site>

